{"lemma":"مِينَةٌ","slug":"مِينَةٌ","root":"#.ن.#","root_slug":"_-ن-_","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ن-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1307","n43481"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"port, harbor"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alternative form of مِينَا (mīnā)","tags":["alt-of","alternative"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"The form is a مِفْعال (mifʕāl) from the verb أَنَى (ʔanā, “to draw near”). Nevertheless, it is predominantly considered a loanword. Perhaps from Egyptian mjnwt (“harbor”) or mjnt (“mooring post”), related to Egyptian mjnj (“to moor”). Alternatively from Ancient Greek λιμήν (limḗn, “harbour”), whence also Hebrew נמל (nāmēl), with l- reinterpreted as the Arabic article."},"ipa":["/miː.naːʔ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1307","headword_ar":"مَيِنَّةٌ","root":"An","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad., (S, Mgh, K, &c., in the first and last in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA^n","text_ar":"مان"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in the second in the present art.,) where it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a Tuwla","text_ar":"اـِنَّ طُولَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~alaApi waqiSara AlxuTobapi may^in~apN mino fiqohi Alr~ajuli","text_ar":"الصَّلَاةِ وَقِصَرَ الخُطْبَةِ مَيِنَّةٌ مِنْ فِقْهِ الرَّجُلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, TA, &c.,) is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafEilapN waqiSara AlxuTobapi may^in~apN mino fiqohi Alr~ajuli","text_ar":"مَفعِلَةٌ وَقِصَرَ الخُطْبَةِ مَيِنَّةٌ مِنْ فِقْهِ الرَّجُلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^oninapN","text_ar":"مَاْنِنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a","text_ar":"اـِنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Z in the Fáïk, IAth, Mgh, K,) the corroborative particle; (Z, IAth, Mgh;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEosaApN","text_ar":"مَعْسَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EasaY","text_ar":"عَسَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) but not regularly derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a","text_ar":"اـِنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because a word may not be so derived from a particle; or it may be said that this is so derived after the particle has been made a noun; (Z, IAth;) or neither of these modes of derivation is regular: (MF:) the meaning is, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily the longness of the prayer and the shortness of the oration from the pulpit are"},{"kind":"text","text":"(together)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a proper ground for one's saying, Verily the man is a person of knowledge"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, * Mgh, K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA^n","text_ar":"مان"},{"kind":"text","text":":) this is the proper signification: accord. to AO, the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing whereby one learns the knowledge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligence, of the man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing suitable to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and whereby one knows,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the knowledge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligence, of the man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sign"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the knowledge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligence, of the man;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suitable thereto:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an evidence thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an indication,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a symptom, thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"everything that indicates a thing being said to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"may^in~apN lahu","text_ar":"مَيِنَّةٌ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": [so that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"may^in~apN lika*aA","text_ar":"مَيِنَّةٌ لِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be well rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that occasions one's knowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inferring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suspecting, such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a person that occasions one's doing so:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, more properly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing, &c., in which such a thing is usually known to take place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exist,"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZin~apN","text_ar":"مَظِنَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] one of the strangest of the things said of it is, that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a substitute for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Z","text_ar":"ظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZin~apN","text_ar":"مَظِنَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAth:) this seems to have been the opinion of Lh: (Az, L:) accord. to AA, it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=yapN","text_ar":"ا=يَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.) As says (S, * K, TA, all in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA^n","text_ar":"مان"},{"kind":"text","text":") that the word is thus, with teshdeed to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the trad. and in a verse of poetry, as these are related; (S, TA;) but correctly, in his opinion, it should be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"may^iynapN","text_ar":"مَيِينَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylapN","text_ar":"فَعِيلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, * TA,) unless it be from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a","text_ar":"اـِنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as first stated above: (S, TA:) AZ used to say that it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"may^it~apN","text_ar":"مَيِتَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, * TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meet, fit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worthy"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deserving,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEilapN","text_ar":"مَفْعِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^otitapN","text_ar":"مَاْتِتَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^at~ahu","text_ar":"اَتَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “he overcame him with an argument or the like:” (S, K, TA:) but some say that it is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEil~apN","text_ar":"فَعِلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^ana","text_ar":"مَاَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiHotamala","text_ar":"اِحْتَمَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA^n","text_ar":"مان"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K in that art.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa may^in~apN liloxayori","text_ar":"هُوَ مَيِنَّةٌ لِلْخَيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a","text_ar":"اـِنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is a person fit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper, for one's saying of him, Verily he is good;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEosaApN","text_ar":"مَعْسَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EasaY","text_ar":"عَسَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", as meaning “a person fit, or proper, for one's saying of him, May-be he will do good.” (A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu lamay^in~apN A^ano yakuwna ka*aA","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَمَيِنَّةٌ اَنْ يَكُونَ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily it is meet, fit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper, for one's saying of it, Verily it is thus;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is worthy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deserving, of one's saying"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"verily it is a thing meet, fit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper, for one's saying"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is a thing worthy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deserving, of one's saying"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEilapN","text_ar":"مَفْعِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a","text_ar":"اـِنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K in the present art.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu lamay^in~apN A^ano yafoEala *aAka","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَمَيِنَّةٌ اَنْ يَفْعَلَ ذَاكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is meet, fit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper, for doing that;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is worthy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deserving, of doing that:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"verily he is a person meet, fit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper, for doing that;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is a person worthy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deserving, of doing that:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner you say of two, and of more, and of a female: but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"may^in~apN","text_ar":"مَيِنَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEil~apN","text_ar":"فَعِلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA^n","text_ar":"مان"},{"kind":"text","text":"], i. e. a triliteral-radical word. (M.) ―         -b2-  You also say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ataAhu Ealay may^n~ap *aAka","text_ar":"اَتَاهُ عَلَي مَينَّة ذَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came to him at the time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"season,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fit"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of that;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the first thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)"}],"source_refs":["MF","Mgh","S","As","K","M","IAth","Az","L","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n43481","headword_ar":"مَيِنَّةٌ","root":"mA^n","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"An","text_ar":"ان"},{"kind":"text","text":", where will be found the explanations of this word given in the S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA^n","text_ar":"مان"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}